12/11/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Judicial sector employees may stage a strike, justice sector trade union head Slavica Zivanovic announced on Friday (November 9th).
The union is demanding a 100% wage increase for administrative personnel in the sector.
Zivanovic added that for now, the administrative staff will only deal with high priority cases, but if negotiations with the government fail, a general strike will be called.
(B92, RTS, Tanjug - 09/11/07)
